      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(telegram): allow expandable blockquotes",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Problem: `<blockquote expandable>` is stripped in Telegram HTML output. `blockquote` lives in `TELEGRAM_SIMPLE_HTML_TAGS`, which only permits the tag with zero attributes, so the `expandable` attribute fails sanitization.\n- Why it matters: Telegram natively supports expandable blockquotes; agents can't emit them today.\n- What changed: Move `blockquote` from the simple-tag set to `TELEGRAM_ATTR_HTML_TAG_PATTERNS` with pattern `/^(\\s+expandable)?\\s*$/`, which accepts both `<blockquote>` and `<blockquote expandable>`.\n- What did NOT change: All other tags; plain `<blockquote>` and `</blockquote>` still pass.\n\n## Change Type\n\n- [x] Bug fix\n\n## Real behavior proof\n\n- Behavior addressed: expandable blockquotes now survive Telegram HTML sanitization.\n- Real environment tested: OpenClaw Telegram channel, agent reply containing `<blockquote expandable>...</blockquote>`.\n- Before: the `expandable` attribute was dropped, message rendered as a normal (non-collapsible) blockquote.\n- After: message renders as a collapsible/expandable blockquote in the Telegram client.\n- Not tested: nested blockquotes (unchanged behavior).\n\n## Note\n\nAI-assisted, single-line change.",
